            "metadata": {
                "abstract": "Sequencing of transposon insertion libraries is used to determine the relative fitness of individual mutants at a large scale. However, there is a lack of tools for specifically analyzing data from such experiments with paired sample designs. Here, we introduce CAFE - Coefficient-based Analysis of Fitness by read Enrichment - a software package that can analyze data from paired transposon mutant sequencing experiments, generate fitness coefficients for each gene and condition and perform appropriate statistical testing on these fitness coefficients.",
